[1] Cholera - Angola
Date: Thu, 7 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200609/07/eng20060907_300638.html>

The WHO has announced that a total of 53 537 cumulative cases and
2187 deaths have been reported in 15 out of the 18 provinces in
Angola, since the beginning of the outbreak on 13 Feb 2006.
According to a press notice published by the WHO on Wed, 6 Sep 2006,
from 27 Aug to 3 Sep 2006, the number of weekly cases increased from
218 to 358. In this same period, the number of deaths also increased
from 4 to 6, with case fatality rate of 1.7 percent.
The province of Namibe with 238 cases per week is the most affected,
followed by Kuando Kubango with 22 cases and Uige with 19. In this
week, the provinces of Benguela, Luanda, Kwanza Norte and Kwanza Sul
reported 14 cases each.
This year's outbreak of the water-borne disease in Angola has been
acknowledged by international relief organizations to be the
country's worst since independence over 3 decades ago.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
