[2] Cholera - Angola
Date: Thu, 7 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=470423>

According to the Ministry of Health`s daily bulletin, 27 new cases of
cholera were registered in 4 provinces of the country, from 2 to 3
Sep 2006.
According to the document, the southwestern Namibe Province has the
highest number with 22 cases, followed by Kuando Kubango (south) with
3, while Luanda (north-central) and Kwanza Norte (north) had 1 case
during the mentioned period.
Luanda continues to lead the list, with 23 546 cases and 309 deaths,
followed by Benguela with 8523. In Malanje Province, with
information up to 3 Sep 2006 a total of 4 202 cases and 245 deaths.
The central Bie Province recorded 25 cases and 3 deaths, and Huambo
with 15 cases and 5 deaths are the least affected of the 15 provinces
where the cholera outbreak is seriously affecting the population.
Meanwhile, the central Huambo province has the highest mortality rate
with 33 percent, while Luanda has the lowest rate with 1 percent.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Both of the above posts state that 15 of the 18 provinces were
affected. A previous cholera update on ProMED (20060825.2393)
contained a posting which said that the other 3 provinces (Cunene,
Moxico, and Lunda Sul) had cases, but numbers were not given. A map
of Angola showing the location of the provinces can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. -
