[4] Cholera - Uganda (Yumbe)
Date: 4 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Monitor [edited]
<http://www.monitor.co.ug/news/reg09051.php>

Cholera has claimed 7 lives since the disease broke out in Yumbe
district 2 weeks ago.
Speaking during the district cholera task force meeting on Fri, 1 Sep
2006, the Head of Cholera Surveillance, Dr Alfred Yayi, said 4 deaths
occurred at the health center while the other 3 people died in their
homes.
Yayi said by 31 Aug 2006, the district had registered a total of 59
cholera cases, out of which 52 patients were discharged. He said also
2 others were admitted at Apo Health Center.
"On Thu, 31 Aug 2006, we received 2 female patients from Banika and
Wororo villages who are still [hospitalized in] the treatment
center," he said.
[Byline: Kefa Atibuni]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Yumbe is in extreme northwestern Uganda. Its location can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf> - Mod.LL]
